        "title": "Add Entroly context compression skill",
        "body": "## What this PR adds\n\nAdds an **Entroly** skill to the skills directory — a local context compression engine that reduces LLM input tokens by 70-95% on large repos.\n\n### How it works\n- Ranks repo files by query relevance (BM25 + entropy + dependency graph)\n- Selects optimal files under token budget (knapsack optimization)\n- Compresses noisy context while keeping originals recoverable (CCR handles)\n- Aligns cache prefixes for provider discounts (Anthropic 90%, OpenAI 50%)\n- WITNESS hallucination guard checks answers (, ~3ms)\n\n### Usage with OpenClaw\nWorks in proxy mode (transparent to workers), wrap mode (per-worker), or as an MCP server. No changes needed to existing worker prompts.\n\nApache-2.0, local-first, no outbound analytics by default.\n\n**GitHub**: https://github.com/juyterman1000/entroly",
